Q4: Compile Project in Jenkins using Maven — Steps

Install Jenkins and ensure it is running at http://localhost:8080
.

Install Maven Integration Plugin from Manage Jenkins → Plugins.

Configure Maven in Manage Jenkins → Tools → Maven installations → Add Maven → Save.

Configure JDK in Manage Jenkins → Tools → JDK installations → Add JDK → Save.

Create a new Maven project using New Item → Maven project → OK.

Configure Source Code Management (Git URL if needed).

In Build section, select configured Maven and set goals as clean install.

Save the job configuration.

Click Build Now and verify Console Output for successful Maven build.


Q5: Create Slave Node (Agent) in Jenkins — Steps

Go to Manage Jenkins → Nodes → New Node.

Enter node name, select Permanent Agent → OK.

Set Remote Root Directory path on the agent machine.

Set Launch Method as “Launch agent via Java Web Start/Agent.jar”.

Save and download agent.jar from the node page.

Copy agent.jar to the agent machine.

Run java -jar agent.jar -jnlpUrl <URL> -secret <secretKey> to connect the agent.

Confirm node status shows as “Connected” in Jenkins Dashboard.

Q6Assign Project to Slave Node and Build Project
Create a new Maven project using New Item → Maven Project → OK.

Configure Git repository (or local pom.xml project uploaded into workspace).

In Build section set Maven goals as clean install → Save.

Create a new Permanent Agent in Manage Jenkins → Nodes → New Node.

Set Remote Root Directory and Launch method → Save.

Download agent.jar from node page and run: java -jar agent.jar -jnlpUrl <URL> -secret <secretKey>.

Verify node status becomes Connected.

Edit the Maven job → Enable “Restrict where this project can be run”.

Enter the Agent Node Label → Save.

Click Build Now.

Verify Console Output shows build executed on the Agent.
